<dec f='halide/build/include/HalideRuntimeOpenCL.h' l='54' type='const char * halide_opencl_get_platform_name(void * user_context)'/>
<doc f='halide/build/include/HalideRuntimeOpenCL.h' l='48'>/** Halide calls this to get the desired OpenCL platform
 * name. Implement this yourself to use a different platform per
 * user_context. The default implementation returns the value set by
 * halide_set_ocl_platform_name, or the value of the environment
 * variable HL_OCL_PLATFORM_NAME. The output is valid until the next
 * call to halide_set_ocl_platform_name. */</doc>
